ProtoDefines:
. "The Cauchy product of $\sum_{n=0^\infty a_n$ and\/} 
   $\sum_{n=0}^\infty b_n$ is $\sum_{n=0}^\infty c_n$, where $ 
   c_n=a_0b_n+a_1b_{n-1}+\cdots+a_{n-1}b_1+a_nb_0. $ Thus, 
   $c_n$ is the sum of all products $a_ib_j$, where $i\ge0$, 
   $j\ge0$, and $i+j=n$; thus, $ c_n=\sum_{r=0}^n 
   a_rb_{n-r}=\sum_{r=0}^n b_ra_{n-r}. $"
